&lt;p>Batch files are scripts that contain a series of commands to be executed by the command-line interpreter. These files can automate repetitive tasks and enhance productivity. In this article, we&amp;rsquo;ll explore creating batch files to set environment variables and execute shell commands in Windows, PowerShell, and Ubuntu, along with additional scripting nuances.&lt;/p></description></item></channel></rss>